<HEADLINE>
GALAXY VS. WIZARDS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
 
__ Time: 5:30 p.m. at Arrowhead Stadium. 
!tvspt2!TV/Radio: KRLA_AM (1110), KTNQ-AM (1020), Channel 52. 
__ Galaxy (4-3) update: For a team looking to score goals any way
it can get them, it doesn't help that Clint Mathis is unavailable
because of a red-card suspension and Cobi Jones is questionable
because of a sore left toe. Welton, however, is listed as probable
after recovering from a sore ankle that caused him to miss the last
three games. If neither Jones nor Welton can play, the Galaxy might
look to rarely used forwards Lawrence Lozzano or rookie Marvin
Quijano. . . . Goalkeeper Kevin Hartman is looking to extend his
two-game shutout streak. Hartman, who has three shutouts this
season, moved to second place among goalkeepers with a 0.57 goals
against average. 
__ Wizards (0-7) update: By far the worst team in the league,
Kansas City has only scored two goals this season. The Wizards, who
acquired well-known Americans Alexi Lalas and goalkeeper Tony Meola
before the season, have given up a Western Conference-worst 12
goals. The poor start forced longtime coach Ron Newman to quit last
month. Bob Gansler, who coached the 1990 U.S. World Cup team, will
make his debut this afternoon. 

<TEXT>
