<P>
   &UR; Commentary &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports column on the Jets in the
wake of Leon Hess' death. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-RHODEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports column on the first game of
the Knicks-Heat series. Early column on Allan Houston, who was
raised to be an unselfish player and now finds himself being
criticized for being so. To be subbed after the game. By William C.
Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports column on the travails of
small-market baseball clubs. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   LIPSYTE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Yelling, ``Sports, sports, don't you
get it, everything in Glen Ridge is sports,'' a teen-age Jeremiah
runs through a forgettable television movie Monday night with an
inescapable message: Love it, hate it or try to ignore it, jock
culture haunts our national daydreams. By Robert Lipsyte.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Features &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER-MOMS (Undated) _ Joy Fawcett and Carla Overbeck were
pioneers as American soccer players, star defenders on teams that
won a world championship in 1991 and an Olympic gold medal in 1996,
and now they are plowing new cultural ground as soccer-playing
moms. The two players have sought to secure from U.S. Soccer, the
national governing body, some of the rights that women have
attained in the corporate workplace, such as maternity leave and
child care. By Jere Longman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Baseball notes and news: Lead item on
Fernando Tatis, the rising star of the St. Louis Cardinals. By
Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ NBA notes and news. Lead item: An
Indiana-Utah final is generally seen as a prime-time nightmare for
NBC: two small-market, veteran teams with declining vertical leaps,
vying for pro basketball's championship a year after Michael
Jordan's farewell tour. A series without Kobe Bryant, Shaquille
O'Neal, Patrick Ewing or Pat Riley would seem to point to fewer
viewers. But the network contends that it is not playing favorites,
that small-market teams can sell under the right circumstances. By
Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-HASEK (Boston) _ An interview with `The Dominator,` goalie
Dominik Hasek, who came up uncharacteristically mortal in Game One
of the Eastern Conference semifinal between his Buffalo Sabres and
the Boston Bruins. By Robin Finn.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Saturday Games and Events &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-HEAT (Miami) _ Knicks vs. Heat, Game 1, 12:30 p.m. By
Selena Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   W/sidebar by Mike Wise.
</P>
