<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Sunday, May 9. If you have
any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
CHINA-DONATE _ Johnny Chung, the Chinese American at the center of
a Democratic fundraising scandal, has told congressional
investigators that a former U.S. embassy official in Beijing
received a bag of cash from a Chinese beer company executive. Chung
is expected to tell a House committee on Tuesday that he saw an
executive of the Haomen Group Company hand the money to Charles
Parish, who ran the embassy's visa section from 1994 to 1996.
Chung's testimony before the House Committee on Government Reform
and Oversight is expected to center on Chinese attempts to funnel
money to the 1996 Clinton-Gore campaign. By JERRRY KAMMER. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
PUMP (undated) _ Sometimes Sherry Steiner runs her fingers lightly
over her the face of her 15-year-old Jeffrey, who suffers from
severe cerebral palsy. He is racked by nearly continuous muscle
spasms that only an implanted pump and medication can halt. Getting
that pump _ for which they finally received authorization last week
_ had for been the focus of his parents' lives. By MAUREEN WEST.
Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
NAVAJO-SHEEP (undated) _ My view is breathtaking. Outside my
window, red buttes and deep purple mesas sweep skyward to the
sapphire heavens. The Kaibab mountains snake across the horizon
before ducking into the Grand Canyon. The silent land is
interrupted only by a meadowlark's song. Vacation? Nope, this is
Navajo sheepherding _ urban style. My view is from the seat of my
4X4 truck. My mother, Dorothy Reed, and Aunt Jeanette's tiny herd
of 17 goats and three sheep, graze below. By BETTY REID. Story will
move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) _ When I was a boy my mother used to tell
me that, someday, if God and the Blessed Virgin Mary paid attention
to her prayers, my brother and I would become orphans. About a
month and a half ago, we finally got lucky. I guess. By E.J.
MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories.
</P>
