<HEADER>
A9573 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-SPURS-HNS &LR;      05-08 0712
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-SPURS-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Spurs realize Minnesota offers daunting challenge during
first-round matchup
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By TERRY BLOUNT &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 1999, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ As the hottest team in the NBA, the San Antonio
Spurs are expected to use and abuse the Minnesota Timberwolves in a
warm-up series to set up bigger and better things yet to come in
the NBA playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The opening-round series that starts today in the Alamodome
sounds easy enough for the top seed in the Western Conference, but
these pesky Wolves haven't exactly been easy pickings for the Spurs
this season.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota was 2-2 against San Antonio this year. The Spurs
easily defeated the Timberwolves 95-79 at the Alamodome on April
14, but Minnesota's leading scorer Kevin Garnett and point guard
Terrell Brandon did not play in that game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Minnesota is a very athletic team and they're tough,'' said
Spurs forward Tim Duncan. ``We had some problems with them this
season, but most of those games came early. We are playing a lot
better now than we were then.''
</P>
<P>
   The Spurs (37-13) were 1-2 against Minnesota in the first 14
games of the season when San Antonio went 6-8. The Spurs are 31-5
since the slow start.
</P>
<P>
   But this is a different Minnesota team than the Spurs have seen,
starting with Brandon. Stephon Marbury was traded to New Jersey at
midseason, leaving the Wolves in a transition period with Brandon.
</P>
<P>
   ``Anytime you bring in a great player like Terrell, it takes a
while to get the chemistry working,'' said Spurs guard Mario Elie.
``I think they lost a little of their edge when Marbury left
because he worked well with KG.''
</P>
<P>
   But Garnett also has been adjusting to other new players around
him this year. Forward Tom Gugliotti, a major cog in the team's
success last season, signed with Phoenix in the offseason. Joe
Smith is the other starting forward now.
</P>
<P>
   The trio of Garnett, Gugliotti and Marbury led the Wolves to a
45-37 record last season. But the nucleus of Garnett, Smith and
Brandon was learning about each other on the run while the team
finished 25-25 this year in the lockout-shortened season.
</P>
<P>
   The Timberwolves have had their impressive moments, including
two victories over San Antonio when they held Duncan to a total of
18 points. The MVP candidate averaged only 14 points a game against
the Wolves, who often would double-team him with Garnett and Smith.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've been strong against me,'' Duncan said. ``But hopefully
I can pass off and make them pay if they double team me this
time.''
</P>
<P>
   Duncan and center David Robinson have been the best low-post duo
in the league over the last three weeks. Robinson averaged 20.8
points, 13 rebounds and 2.2 blocks when the Spurs won four games
over the last five days of the regular season to earn the No. 1
seed in the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   San Antonio coach Gregg Popovich was concerned about how the
grind of the final week would affect his team, but the playoff
schedule gave the Spurs a much-needed three-day rest for the first
time since the abbreviated season began.
</P>
<P>
   ``After going through that final stretch, we were worried we
wouldn't have anything left for the playoffs,'' Popovich said.
``And we will need all our energy in this series because Minnesota
has the hardest-working team in the league. They are constantly
working on the court.''
</P>
<P>
   The Spurs have some new faces this year who understand about the
work-ethic required in the playoffs. Elie, guard Steve Kerr and
forward Jerome Kersey have played in a total of 296 playoff games,
the same amount as the rest of the team combined.
</P>
<P>
   The veteran trio also has done what the other Spurs have not
done by playing and winning in the NBA Finals. Elie was part of
both Houston championships, Kerr played on three of Chicago's title
years, and Kersey was on a Portland team that reached the Finals in
1990 and 1992.
</P>
<P>
   Elie has been the vocal leader all season for the Spurs, a role
he plans to continue in the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told the guys, `It just takes 15 more wins and we're the
champions,''' Elie said. ``We're peaking at the right time. The
guys are feeling good about each other and we like our chances.
This is it. Now you start counting them down.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
